        "text": "*[Bug 19075] New: `cairo_pdf(onefile = TRUE)` fails to create another page after drawing multiple glyphs in a masked viewport*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19075>\n\n            Bug ID: 19075\n           Summary: `cairo_pdf(onefile = TRUE)` fails to create another\n                    page after drawing multiple glyphs in a masked\n                    viewport\n           Product: R\n           Version: R-devel (trunk)\n          Hardware: Other\n                OS: All\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Graphics\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:trevor.l.davis@gmail.com|trevor.l.davis@gmail.com>\n\nCreated attachment 3701\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3701&amp;action=edit>\nReproducible example of cairo_pdf bug\n\nI ran into a bug with `cairo_pdf(onefile = TRUE)` where `grid.newpage()` failed\nto  create a second page after I drew a `glyphGrob()` with multiple glyphs\nwithin a viewport with an alpha mask.\n\nConditions required to trigger the bug:\n\n1. `cairo_pdf(onefile = TRUE)`\n2. Draw a `glyphGrob` with &gt;= 2 glyphs inside a masked viewport\n3. Call `grid.newpage()` plus additional grid drawing commands\n\nDoes NOT occur with:\n\n- `pdf()` instead of `cairo_pdf()`\n- No masked viewport\n- A `glyphGrob()` with only 1 glyph\n- The `glyphGrob()` wrapped in `groupGrob()`\n\nI've attached a reproducible example.  I plan to upload a patch with a proposed\nfix.",
