        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 19075] `cairo_pdf(onefile = TRUE)` fails to create another page after drawing multiple glyphs in a masked viewport*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19075>\n\n--- Comment #1 from Trevor Davis (<mailto:trevor.l.davis@gmail.com|trevor.l.davis@gmail.com>) ---\nCreated attachment 3702\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3702&amp;action=edit>\nFix of `cairo_pdf()` bug\n\n* In `Cairo_Glyph` there is a loop over glyphs\n* `cairoBegin` (which does `cairo_push_group` inside a masked viewport) is\ncalled before the glyph loop\n* Currently `cairoEnd (which does `cairo_pop_group`) is called **inside** the\nloop.  When there are `n &gt;= 2` glyphs there are hence `n` pops against 1 push\nwhich apparently causes an error that silently swallows any `cairo_show_page`\n* The patch moves this `cairoEnd` so it is after this glyph loop so we only\nhave one `cairo_push_group` and one `cairo_pop_group`",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
